  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators aim to test the hypothesis that Laser speckle contrast imaging allows for
      the measurement of cutaneous blood flow following various durations of tourniquet ischemia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Ischemia and post occlusive reactive hyperemia in the skin is tested in healthy normal
      subjects for tourniquet ischemias of 1, 2 &amp; 3 minutes at rest.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
